20/12/2002
PRIZREN, Kosovo, Yugoslavia -- A Bulgarian delegation led by Deputy Chief of the General Staff Vice Adm Peter Petrov arrived Thursday (19 December) in Prizren to conduct inspections of the Bulgarian contingent in KFOR. 
Petrov promised Bulgarian soldiers a positive resolution of their demand for extra payment and congratulated them for their considerable contribution to the mission. 
The 40-member Bulgarian engineering platoon is part of the multinational Southwest brigade under German command. 
The Bulgarian servicemen are responsible for repairing buildings and infrastructure in Kosovo. 
(BTA - 19/12/02)
